com.spears.objects.util

Interface ArrayGrid<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Data type to be stored
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FloatArrayArrayGrid, GenericArrayGrid

    public interface ArrayGrid<T>
extends java.lang.Cloneable
    A generic 2D data structure that functions very much like ArrayList. Used to store large, dense sets of data. The structure is always rectangular.

      • insertColumnAt

        void insertColumnAt(int x,
                    java.util.List<T> col)
        Inserts a column containing the list at the given x coordinate. Will shift any existing data. If the list is taller than the structure the structure will grow.
        Parameters:
        x - Where to add the column
        col - Column of data to add

      • addRow

      • insertRowAt

        void insertRowAt(int y,
                 java.util.List<T> row)

        Parameters:
        y - Where to add the row
